<font color="#FF0000">DAZED AND CONFUSED</font><br>
<tt>Mon May 26 21:59:44 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
My name is Dixie.  I served in the Nam in '73 out of C.R. Bay and Danang...logistics expert.  Yes, I was enlisted; not a nurse (although, as irony has it, I am one now).  Bro's, I feel very lost.  Always have.  No one...I mean NO ONE wants nor cares about my...experiences.  I learned to stuff all of it; nnever share any of it.  Couldn't (and still can't) stand to hear someone say &quot;Oh, you're a Viet Vet?  Well, thank goodness you didn't have to suffer like those men&quot;.  Sounds like I'm a cry baby...but brothers...I wish I WAS.  Maybe I wouldn't feel so...however it is I am feeling right now.  Does anyone have any suggestions for this messed up emotional situation?  Jeez, guys, I don't even make much sense at all.  Funny..it's always that way when I try to talk about the Nam.  Under &quot;normal&quot; circumstances, I am reasonably intelligent.  I would appreciate any comments or further discussion.  Jeez, I can almost hear my NCOIC saying &quot;God, Gillman!!!  Will you get a grip?!&quot;<br><br>
ae033@seorf.ohiou.edu
